😬👩‍🍳 For less confident cooks:

1. Chop and weigh it.

2. Add 1.5x volume of liquid to weight of cheese eg for 100g cheese, add 150ml milk/water. (To work this out for odd amounts just go to the calculator on your phone and type in your cheese weight, and multiply it by 1.5) &gt;&gt;

@Yoxallred Two ways, depending on quantity required.
1. Mash a single canned prune with a tsp or two of butter and a pinch of coarse salt, use a fork to vigorously mix the two together until combined.
2. Bullet blender, entire can of prunes, half a pat of butter, return to fridge to set
